==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triternate
<hw>Tri*ter"nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>ternate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Three times ternate; -- applied to a leaf whose petiole separates
into three branches, each of which divides into three parts which each
bear three leafiets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tritheism</ent>⟦br⟧
